BUSINESS OF THE HOUSE

Mr. St. Laurent moved the adjournment of the house.

He said: Tomorrow I hope we will have unanimous consent to answer the questions on the order paper and to proceed with the notices of motion for the production of papers. Afterward we will continue with this debate and, when it is concluded, take up Bill No. 12 to amend the statutes to adapt them for application to Newfoundland.

Mr. Graydon: And after that?

Mr. St. Laurent: Well, tomorrow is Wed- nesday; I do not think there will be anything after that.

Motion agreed to and the house adjourned at 11.33 pm.
